article.headline: Mond helps Aggies over No. 8 LSU 74-72 in 7 OTs
article.description: Kellen Mond's 2-point conversion to Kendrick Rogers in the seventh overtime gave Texas A&M 74-72 victory over No. 8 LSU on Saturday night in a game that tied the NCAA record for most overtimes in an FBS game.
article.linkText: Mond helps Aggies over No. 8 LSU 74-72 in 7 OTs

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Texas A&M beats LSU in crazy 7th overtime) 2018/11/24 ESHEET SOTFull

article.story: COLLEGE STATION, Texas -- With Texas A&M's game with No. 8 LSU tied at 72-72 in the seventh overtime on Saturday night and the Aggies set to attempt a 2-point conversion, receiver Kendrick Rogers was frantically being tended to on the sideline for severe cramps in his calves. Rogers was able to get himself together just in time to get back in the game and grab Kellen Mond's 2-point conversion pass that gave A&M at 74-72 victory in a game that tied the NCAA record for most overtimes in an FBS game. "These are moments you live for, so no matter what's going on with your body you want to be out there," Rogers said. "So, you just have to talk yourself out of it, just mentally fight through it." Mond connected with Quartney Davis on a 17-yard throw to tie it at 72. Greedy Williams was called for pass interference on the first 2-point conversion try, giving the Aggies (8-4, 5-3, No. 22 CFP), another shot. After a false start by Texas A&M, Mond found Rogers for the conversion to end it. Throngs of fans rushed the field to celebrate after the grab by Rogers. "We showed as a team that we're never going to quit, and we did that for four quarters and way more," Mond said. Joe Burrow had a 10-yard TD run to put LSU (9-3, 5-3, No. 7 CFP) up 72-66 in the seventh OT, but his 2-point conversion throw failed. "You had two teams out there refusing to lose and we just made one more play," Texas A&M coach Jimbo Fisher said. The 74 points LSU allowed are the most ever given up by a ranked team, eclipsing the 73 No. 24 Fresno State gave up to Northern Illinois on Oct. 6, 1990, and the first seven overtime game involving a ranked team. The 146 combined points are the most in an FBS game in NCAA history and the second-most in college football history behind the 161 points Abilene Christian and West Texas A&M scored in Abilene Christian's 93-68 win in 2008. "I lost track of overtimes ... it is the craziest game ever," Fisher said looking a bit dazed. Mond threw for 287 yards and six touchdowns, three 2-point conversions and ran for one more TD as Texas A&M snapped a seven-game skid against LSU and got its first win over the Tigers since 1995. LSU coach Ed Orgeron's clothes might have already dried by the time this one ended after he was prematurely doused with Gatorade after the Tigers appeared to have a clinching interception in the fourth quarter. But the play was reviewed and it was ruled that Mond's knee was down before the throw, keeping the Aggies alive and setting up the wild finish. "The momentum kept on changing both ways and the guys responded," Orgeron said. "That was one heck of an overtime, we just fell one play short. Our guys have nothing to be ashamed about, they fought, they fought hard." Burrow threw for three touchdowns and ran for three more as the Tigers were denied their first 10-win regular season since 2012 and likely knocked out of contention for a New Year's Day bowl game. Mond threw a 25-yard TD pass to Jace Sternberger and a 2-point conversion to Rogers in sextuple overtime before Burrow had a 4-yard touchdown run and Burrow ran for a 4-yard TD and threw for the 2-point conversion to push it to a seventh OT. Clyde Edwards-Helaire took a pitch from Burrow and launched an 11-yard TD pass to Tory Carter to put the Tigers on top in the fifth overtime, but the 2-point conversion failed. Mond answered with a 6-yard throw to Rogers, but A&M's 2-point try failed, too to send it to the sixth OT. Mond found Davis on a 19-yard touchdown pass on the last play of regulation to send it to OT. Orgeron felt like the clock ran out before Mond spiked the ball to stop the clock with 1 second to allow for that play. "I just feel bad for those young men," Orgeron said. "That second shouldn't have been put on the clock, and I'm sticking to that." Both teams kicked field goals in the fourth overtime to send it to the fifth. Burrow threw a 25-yard touchdown pass to Dee Anderson in triple overtime and Justin Jefferson grabbed the 2-point conversion. Rogers made it 49-49 and forced quadruple overtime when he grabbed a 25-yard TD pass and the 2-point conversion. Both teams settled for field goals in the first overtime. Mond had a 3-yard touchdown run in double overtime and LSU sent it to triple OT when Nick Brossette followed with a 3-yard run, too. THE TAKEAWAY This was a game for the ages and one that both teams will remember for a long time. POLL IMPLICATIONS LSU will likely fall a few spots in the poll after that loss. POST-GAME ALTERCATION A photographer for The Baton Rouge Advocate tweeted a photo of LSU director of player personnel Kevin Faulk and a man they say had what appears to be an Aggie bench credential in a physical altercation after the game. Fisher was asked who the second person was and if he knew about the incident after the game and said: "I have no idea." THEY SAID IT Rogers on what he thought about Aggie fans storming the field after the win: "I wasn't expecting it and I just saw a lot of kids come up and hug me and I was like: `what the heck is going on?" UP NEXT Both teams will wait to see where they'll be heading for their bowl games. --- More AP college football: https://apnews.com/tag/Collegefootball and https://twitter.com/AP-Top25

videos.headline: Williams takes on two LSU defenders for 10-yard TD
videos.description: Trayveon Williams finds a seam and bulldozes his way through two defenders to reach the end zone, giving the Aggies a 7-0 lead over the Tigers.

videos.headline: QB Burrow ties it up with 22-yard TD run
videos.description: Joe Burrow keeps it himself and bursts through a hole, getting all the way to the end zone to knot the score at 7-7 against the Aggies.

videos.headline: Mond throws strike for 10-yard TD pass
videos.description: Jace Sternberger runs a crossing route at the goal line, and Kellen Mond puts it on the money to put the Aggies back on top, 14-7.

videos.headline: WR Jefferson wins jump ball for game-tying TD
videos.description: Joe Burrow puts it up for Justin Jefferson, who rips it away from Debione Renfro for the 7-yard touchdown pass to knot the score at 17-17.

videos.headline: LSU muffs punt, A&M pounces on it
videos.description: Jonathan Giles can't handle Braden Mann's punt, and Buddy Johnson falls on it to set up the Aggies' go-ahead touchdown drive.

videos.headline: Aggies reclaim lead with 1-yard TD run
videos.description: Trayveon Williams gets through a hole and scores easily to give Texas A&M a 24-17 lead over the Tigers.

videos.headline: LSU scoops and scores to tie game in 4th quarter
videos.description: Trayveon Williams tries to fight for extra yards, but he coughs it up, and Michael Divinity Jr. returns it 58 yards to tie the game at 24-24.

videos.headline: Tigers take lead with 14-yard TD pass
videos.description: Joe Burrow steps up in the pocket and completes a pass to Foster Moreau, who barrels through an A&M defender to cross the goal line and give LSU a 31-24 lead.

videos.headline: Aggies force OT with last-second TD pass
videos.description: Kellen Mond threads the needle and connects with a leaping Quartney Davis for the game-tying 19-yard touchdown as time expires in regulation.

videos.headline: Mond begins 2nd OT with 3-yard TD run
videos.description: Kellen Mond keeps it himself and gets to the outside, lunging to the end zone to give the Aggies a 41-34 lead at the start of the 2nd overtime.

videos.headline: LSU forces triple overtime with 3-yard TD run
videos.description: Nick Brossette takes the handoff on 4th-and-2 and spins his way to the goal line, reaching the ball across the plane to tie the game at 41-41 in overtime.

videos.headline: Burrow tosses 25-yard TD pass to start 3rd OT
videos.description: Joe Burrow lets it fly down the sideline, hitting Dee Anderson in stride for the go-ahead touchdown to make it 49-41 Tigers after the 2-point conversion.

videos.headline: Rogers makes one-handed catch, hauls in 2-pt conversion to force 4th OT
videos.description: Kellen Mond throws one up to Kendrick Rogers, who makes an incredible one-handed catch in the end zone, then makes a leaping catch for the game-tying 2-point conversion.

videos.headline: Edwards-Helaire's HB toss gives LSU lead in 5th OT
videos.description: RB Clyde Edwards-Helaire and sets his feet to throw and finds a wide-open Tory Carter for the 11-yard touchdown pass, making it 58-52 Tigers in the 5th overtime.

videos.headline: Aggies answer with 6-yard TD pass
videos.description: Kellen Mond throws on the run to connect with Kendrick Rogers in the end zone, tying the game at 58-58 and extending the game to a 6th overtime.

videos.headline: Aggies jump ahead in 6th OT with 25-yard TD pass, 2-point conversion
videos.description: Kellen Mond leads Jace Sternberger down the sideline for a 25-yard touchdown, then connects with Kendrick Rogers for the 2-point conversion to make it 66-58 Tigers.

videos.headline: Burrow forces 7th OT with TD run, 2-point conversion
videos.description: Joe Burrow charges up the middle for a 4-yard touchdown run, then throws on target to Dee Anderson to tie the game at 66-66 and force overtime number 7.

videos.headline: Burrow starts 7th OT with 10-yard TD run
videos.description: Joe Burrow spins out of tackles and takes it to the house, making it 72-66 Tigers at the start of the 7th overtime.

videos.headline: Texas A&M tops LSU in record-tying 7 OTs
videos.description: Texas A&M forces OT on a last-second touchdown then prevails in the seventh overtime, tied for most in FBS history, on a two-point conversion to beat LSU 74-72.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Texas A&M tops LSU in record-tying 7 OTs) 2018/11/24 ESHEET SC

videos.headline: LSU celebrates too early before overturned call.
videos.description: Late in the 4th quarter, Texas A&M's Kellen Mond throws an interception. LSU celebrates, but replay overturns the call because Mond's knee was down.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (LSU celebrates too early before overturned call) 2018/11/24 ESHEET

videos.headline: Texas A&M takes sigh of relief after 2-point conversion in 7th OT
videos.description: Texas A&M QB Kellen Mond fires a 2-point conversion to Kendrick Rogers in the seventh overtime to give the Aggies a 74-72 win over LSU.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Texas A&M takes sigh of relief after 2-point conversion in 7th OT) 2018/11/24 ESHEET

videos.headline: Mond says Texas A&M 'never quit' vs. LSU
videos.description: Texas A&M WR Kellen Mond expresses his thoughts on the Aggies outlasting LSU for a 74-72 win after seven overtimes.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Interview (Mond says Texas A&M ‘never quit’ vs. LSU) 2018/11/24

videos.headline: Orgeron says putting 1 second back on clock 'unfair' to LSU
videos.description: LSU head coach Ed Orgeron expresses his frustrations with 1 second being put back on the clock in regulation of their 7-overtime loss to Texas A&M.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Presser (Orgeron says putting 1 second back on clock ‘unfair’ to LSU) 2018/11/24

videos.headline: Fisher says Texas A&M's win vs. LSU is 'about the players'
videos.description: Texas A&M head coach Jimbo Fisher expresses how proud he is of his players after defeating LSU in 7 overtimes.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Presser (Fisher says Texas A&M’s win vs. LSU is ‘about the players’) 2018/11/24
